  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I saw no women where I went.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Whether there were women there, I, I was not aware, no.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, most of them were, at that time, organizing details to clean out the SS barracks, which were nearby.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had some rather, well, sturdy barracks that they planned on using as a hospital routine.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the order was to transfer those that were living into those quarters where they could receive some nutritional support and medical treatment that we might be able to provide at that time.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I did not participate in that particular group.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The chief surgeon was involved a little bit in contacting the doctors who were in their own hospital there, many of whom were prisoners themselves.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was my understanding they had done some experimentation on typhus.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were looking at some of the patients in the, in the hospital itself, and those were the really bad ones, the open wounds.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I can remember yet seeing the legs wrapped in what looked like, to me, toilet tissue.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that was their traditional wrapping of a wound.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He got into a discussion with one of the doctors there, and they had never heard of penicillin.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And of course, that was new to us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So he asked me if I would go with him, and they'd give a demonstration on the use of penicillin and what it would do.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we had a limited amount we were able to give to them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at that time, penicillin didn't come in the little vials like we see them now.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
